name: Polymer
comment:
The mixin class for Polymer elements. It provides convenience features on top of the custom elements web standard.

If this class is used as a mixin, you must call polymerCreated() from the body of your constructor.

$.comment: Map of items in the shadow root(s) by their nuxeo_api_playground/nx_operation.Element.id.

shadowRoots.name: shadowRoots
shadowRoots.comment:
Gets the shadow root associated with the corresponding custom element.

This is identical to shadowRoot, unless there are multiple levels of inheritance and they each have their own shadow root. For example, this can happen if the base class and subclass both have <template> tags in their <polymer-element> tags.

childNodes.name: childNodes
childNodes.comment:
A list of this node's children.

Other resources

  • Node.childNodes from MDN.

firstChild.name: firstChild
firstChild.comment:
The first child of this node.

Other resources

  • Node.firstChild from MDN.

lastChild.name: lastChild
lastChild.comment:
The last child of this node.

Other resources

  • Node.lastChild from MDN.

nextNode.name: nextNode
nextNode.comment:
The next sibling node.

Other resources

  • Node.nextSibling from MDN.

nodeName.name: nodeName
nodeName.comment:
The name of this node.

This varies by this node's nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Node.nodeType.

Other resources

  • Node.nodeName from MDN. This page contains a table of nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Node.nodeName values for each nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Node.nodeType.

nodeType.name: nodeType
nodeType.comment:
The type of node.

This value is one of:

  • nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Node.ATTRIBUTE_NODE if this node is an attribute.
  • [CDATA_SECTION_NODE] if this node is a nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.CDataSection.
  • nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Node.COMMENT_NODE if this node is a nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.Comment.
  • [DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE] if this node is a nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.DocumentFragment.
  • nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Node.DOCUMENT_NODE if this node is a nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.Document.
  • [DOCUMENT_TYPE_NODE] if this node is a DocumentType node.
  • nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Node.ELEMENT_NODE if this node is an nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Element.
  • nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Node.ENTITY_NODE if this node is an entity.
  • [ENTITY_REFERENCE_NODE] if this node is an entity reference.
  • nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Node.NOTATION_NODE if this node is a notation.
  • [PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION_NODE] if this node is a nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.ProcessingInstruction.
  • nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Node.TEXT_NODE if this node is a nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.Text node.

Other resources

  • Node.nodeType from MDN.

nodeValue.name: nodeValue
nodeValue.comment:
The value of this node.

This varies by this type's nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Node.nodeType.

Other resources

  • Node.nodeValue from MDN. This page contains a table of nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Node.nodeValue values for each nuxeo_api_playground/nx_structures_browser.Node.nodeType.

ownerDocument.name: ownerDocument
ownerDocument.comment:
The document this node belongs to.

Returns null if this node does not belong to any document.

Other resources

  • Node.ownerDocument from MDN.

parent.name: parent
parent.comment:
The parent element of this node.

Returns null if this node either does not have a parent or its parent is not an element.

Other resources

  • Node.parentElement from W3C.

parentNode.name: parentNode
parentNode.comment:
The parent node of this node.

Other resources

  • Node.parentNode from MDN.

previousNode.name: previousNode
previousNode.comment:
The previous sibling node.

Other resources

  • Node.previousSibling from MDN.

text.name: text
text.comment:
All text within this node and its decendents.

Other resources

  • Node.textContent from MDN.

draggable.name: draggable
draggable.comment:
Indicates whether the element can be dragged and dropped.

Other resources

  • Drag and drop sample based on the tutorial from HTML5Rocks.

  • Drag and drop specification from WHATWG.

dropzone.name: dropzone
dropzone.comment:
A set of space-separated keywords that specify what kind of data this Element accepts on drop and what to do with that data.

Other resources

  • Drag and drop sample based on the tutorial from HTML5Rocks.

  • Drag and drop specification from WHATWG.

hidden.name: hidden
hidden.comment:
Indicates whether the element is not relevant to the page's current state.

Other resources

  • Hidden attribute specification from WHATWG.

translate.name: translate
translate.comment:
Specifies whether this element's text content changes when the page is localized.

Other resources

  • The translate attribute from WHATWG.

bindings.name: bindings
bindings.comment:
Gets the data bindings that are associated with this node, if any.

This starts out null, and if nuxeo_api_playground/template_binding.enableBindingsReflection is enabled, calls to nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.bind will initialize this field and the binding.

element.name: element
element.comment: The most derived <polymer-element> declaration for this element.

eventController.name: eventController
eventController.comment: Returns the object that should be used as the event controller for event bindings in this element's template. If set, this will override the normal controller lookup.

onReady.name: onReady
onReady.comment: Future indicating that the Polymer library has been loaded and is ready for use.

preventDispose.name: preventDispose
preventDispose.comment: By default the data bindings will be cleaned up when this custom element is detached from the document. Overriding this to return true will prevent that from happening.

syntax.name: syntax
syntax.comment: Use to override the default syntax for polymer-elements. By default this will be null, which causes nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.instanceTemplate to use the template's bindingDelegate or the element.syntax, in that order.

templateInstance.name: templateInstance
templateInstance.comment: Gets the template instance that instantiated this node, if any.

waitingFor.name: waitingFor
waitingFor.comment: Returns a list of elements that have had polymer-elements created but are not yet ready to register. The list is an array of element definitions.

addHostListeners.name: addHostListeners
addHostListeners.comment: Attach event listeners on the host (this) element.

async.name: async
async.comment:
Invokes a function asynchronously. The context of the callback function is function is bound to 'this' automatically. Returns a handle which may be passed to cancelAsync to cancel the asynchronous call.

If you would prefer to run the callback after a given duration, see the nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.asyncTimer method.

If you would like to cancel this, use nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.cancelAsync.

asyncTimer.name: asyncTimer
asyncTimer.comment:
Invokes a function asynchronously. This will call Polymer.flush() and then return a new Timer with the provided nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.asyncTimer.method and nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.asyncTimer.timeout.

If you would prefer to run the callback using window.requestAnimationFrame, see the nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.async method.

To cancel, call nuxeo_api_playground/dart:async.Timer.cancel on the result of this method.

asyncUnbindAll.name: asyncUnbindAll
asyncUnbindAll.comment: Called at detached time to signal that an element's bindings should be cleaned up. This is done asynchronously so that users have the chance to call cancelUnbindAll to prevent unbinding.

attached.name: attached
attached.comment:
Called by the DOM when this element has been inserted into the live document.

More information can be found in the Custom Elements draft specification.

attributeChanged.name: attributeChanged
attributeChanged.comment: Called by the DOM whenever an attribute on this has been changed.

attributeToProperty.name: attributeToProperty
attributeToProperty.comment: If attribute nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.attributeToProperty.name is mapped to a property, deserialize nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.attributeToProperty.value into that property.

bind.name: bind
bind.comment: Called by TemplateBinding/NodeBind to setup a binding to the given property. It's overridden here to support property bindings in addition to attribute bindings that are supported by default.

bindFinished.name: bindFinished
bindFinished.comment: Called by TemplateBinding when all bindings on an element have been executed. This signals that all element inputs have been gathered and it's safe to ready the element, create shadow-root and start data-observation.

bindProperty.name: bindProperty
bindProperty.comment:
Bind the nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.bindProperty.name property in this element to bindable. Note in Dart it is necessary to also define the field:

var myProperty;

ready() {
  super.ready();
  bindProperty(#myProperty,
      new PathObserver(this, 'myModel.path.to.otherProp'));
}

cancelUnbindAll.name: cancelUnbindAll
cancelUnbindAll.comment: / Call in detached to prevent the element from unbinding when it is / detached from the dom. The element is unbound as a cleanup step that / allows its memory to be reclaimed. If cancelUnbindAll is used, consider calling unbindAll when the element is no longer needed. This will allow its memory to be reclaimed.

classFollows.name: classFollows
classFollows.comment: Remove nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.classFollows.className from nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.classFollows.old, add class to nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.classFollows.anew, if they exist.

createPropertyObserver.name: createPropertyObserver
createPropertyObserver.comment: Creates a CompoundObserver to observe property changes. NOTE, this is only done if there are any properties in the _observe object.

deliverPropertyChanges.name: deliverPropertyChanges
deliverPropertyChanges.comment: Force any pending property changes to synchronously deliver to handlers specified in the observe object. Note: normally changes are processed at microtask time.

detached.name: detached
detached.comment:
Called by the DOM when this element has been removed from the live document.

More information can be found in the Custom Elements draft specification.

dispatchMethod.name: dispatchMethod
dispatchMethod.comment: Calls methodOrCallback with nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.dispatchMethod.args if it is a closure, otherwise, treat it as a method name in nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.dispatchMethod.object, and invoke it.

domReady.name: domReady
domReady.comment: Implement to access custom elements in dom descendants, ancestors, or siblings. Because custom elements upgrade in document order, elements accessed in ready or attached may not be upgraded. When domReady is called, all registered custom elements are guaranteed to have been upgraded.

fetchTemplate.name: fetchTemplate
fetchTemplate.comment:
Given a <polymer-element>, find an associated template (if any) to be used for shadow-root generation.

An element may override this method for custom behavior.

fire.name: fire
fire.comment: Fire a nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.CustomEvent targeting nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.fire.onNode, or this if onNode is not supplied. Returns the new event.

forceReady.name: forceReady
forceReady.comment: Forces polymer to register any pending elements. Can be used to abort waiting for elements that are partially defined.

import.name: import
import.comment:
Loads an HTMLImport for each url specified in the urls array. Notifies when all the imports have loaded by calling the callback function argument. This method can be used to lazily load imports. For example, For example,

Polymer.import(['my-import1.html', 'my-import2.html'])
    .then((_) => print('imports lazily loaded'));

Dart Note: This has very limited support in dart, http://dartbug.com/17873

importElements.name: importElements
importElements.comment:
Loads the set of HTMLImports contained in node. Returns a future that resolves when all the imports have been loaded. This method can be used to lazily load imports. For example, given a template:

<template>
  <link rel="import" href="my-import1.html">
  <link rel="import" href="my-import2.html">
</template>

Polymer.importElements(template.content)
    .then((_) => print('imports lazily loaded'));

Dart Note: This has very limited support in dart, http://dartbug.com/17873

injectBoundHtml.name: injectBoundHtml
injectBoundHtml.comment: Inject HTML which contains markup bound to this element into a target element (replacing target element content).

installControllerStyles.name: installControllerStyles
installControllerStyles.comment: Installs external stylesheets and <style> elements with the attribute polymer-scope='controller' into the scope of element. This is intended to be called during custom element construction.

instanceTemplate.name: instanceTemplate
instanceTemplate.comment:
Creates the document fragment to use for each instance of the custom element, given the <template> node. By default this is equivalent to:

templateBind(template).createInstance(this, polymerSyntax);

Where polymerSyntax is a singleton nuxeo_api_playground/polymer.PolymerExpressions instance.

You can override this method to change the instantiation behavior of the template, for example to use a different data-binding syntax.

lightFromTemplate.name: lightFromTemplate
lightFromTemplate.comment: Utility function that stamps a <template> into light-dom.

makeElementReady.name: makeElementReady
makeElementReady.comment: Deprecated: This is no longer a public method.

marshalNodeReferences.name: marshalNodeReferences
marshalNodeReferences.comment: Locate nodes with id and store references to them in nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.$ hash.

notifyPropertyChanges.name: notifyPropertyChanges
notifyPropertyChanges.comment: Handler for property changes; routes changes to observing methods. Note: array valued properties are observed for array splices.

onMutation.name: onMutation
onMutation.comment:
Returns a future when node changes, or when its children or subtree changes.

Use nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.MutationObserver if you want to listen to a stream of changes.

parseDeclaration.name: parseDeclaration
parseDeclaration.comment:
Perform init-time actions based on static information in the <polymer-element> instance argument.

For example, the standard implementation locates the template associated with the given <polymer-element> and stamps it into a shadow-root to implement shadow inheritance.

An element may override this method for custom behavior.

parseDeclarations.name: parseDeclarations
parseDeclarations.comment:
Walks the prototype-chain of this element and allows specific classes a chance to process static declarations.

In particular, each polymer-element has it's own template. parseDeclarations is used to accumulate all element templates from an inheritance chain.

parseDeclaration static methods implemented in the chain are called recursively, oldest first, with the <polymer-element> associated with the current prototype passed as an argument.

An element may override this method to customize shadow-root generation.

polymerCreated.name: polymerCreated
polymerCreated.comment:
If this class is used as a mixin, this method must be called from inside of the created() constructor.

If this class is a superclass, calling super.created() is sufficient.

propertyForAttribute.name: propertyForAttribute
propertyForAttribute.comment: Return the published property matching name, or null.

readValue.name: readValue
readValue.comment: Helper to implement a property with the given nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.readValue.name. This is used for normal and computed properties. Normal properties can provide the initial value using the nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.readValue.initialValue function. Computed properties ignore nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.readValue.initialValue, their value is derived from the expression in the nuxeo_api_playground/polymer.ComputedProperty annotation that appears above the getter that uses this helper.

ready.name: ready
ready.comment: Lifecycle method called when the element has populated it's shadowRoot, prepared data-observation, and made itself ready for API interaction. To wait until the element has been attached to the default view, use nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.attached or nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.domReady.

register.name: register
register.comment:
Like document.register but for Polymer elements.

Use the nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.register.name to specify custom elment's tag name, for example: "fancy-button" if the tag is used as <fancy-button>.

The nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.register.type is the type to construct. If not supplied, it defaults to nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.PolymerElement.

registerSync.name: registerSync
registerSync.comment: Register a custom element that has no associated <polymer-element>. Unlike nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.register this will always perform synchronous registration and by the time this method returns the element will be available using document.createElement or by modifying the HTML to include the element.

scheduleJob.name: scheduleJob
scheduleJob.comment:
Invoke nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.scheduleJob.callback in nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.scheduleJob.wait, unless the job is re-registered, which resets the timer. If nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.scheduleJob.wait is not supplied, this will use window.requestAnimationFrame instead of a nuxeo_api_playground/dart:async.Timer.

For example:

_myJob = Polymer.scheduleJob(_myJob, callback);

Returns the newly created job.

shadowFromTemplate.name: shadowFromTemplate
shadowFromTemplate.comment:
Utility function that creates a shadow root from a <template>.

The base implementation will return a nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.ShadowRoot, but you can replace it with your own code and skip ShadowRoot creation. In that case, you should return null.

In your overridden method, you can use nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.instanceTemplate to stamp the template and initialize data binding, and nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.shadowRootReady to intialize other Polymer features like event handlers. It is fine to call shadowRootReady with a node other than a ShadowRoot such as with this.

unbindAll.name: unbindAll
unbindAll.comment: This method should rarely be used and only if cancelUnbindAll has been called to prevent element unbinding. In this case, the element's bindings will not be automatically cleaned up and it cannot be garbage collected by by the system. If memory pressure is a concern or a large amount of elements need to be managed in this way, unbindAll can be called to deactivate the element's bindings and allow its memory to be reclaimed.

writeValue.name: writeValue
writeValue.comment: Helper to implement a setter of a property with the given nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.writeValue.name on a polymer element. This can be used on normal properties and also on computed properties, as long as the expression used for the computed property is assignable (see nuxeo_api_playground/polymer.ComputedProperty).

innerHtml=.name: innerHtml=
innerHtml=.comment:
Parses the HTML fragment and sets it as the contents of this element.

This uses the default sanitization behavior to sanitize the HTML fragment, use nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.setInnerHtml to override the default behavior.

attributes.name: attributes
attributes.comment:
All attributes on this element.

Any modifications to the attribute map will automatically be applied to this element.

This only includes attributes which are not in a namespace (such as 'xlink:href'), additional attributes can be accessed via nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.getNamespacedAttributes.

bindings.name: bindings
bindings.comment:
Gets the data bindings that are associated with this node, if any.

This starts out null, and if nuxeo_api_playground/template_binding.enableBindingsReflection is enabled, calls to nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.bind will initialize this field and the binding.

borderEdge.name: borderEdge
borderEdge.comment:
Access the dimensions and position of this element's content + padding + border box.

This returns a rectangle with the dimenions actually available for content in this element, in pixels, regardless of this element's box-sizing property. Unlike nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.getBoundingClientRect, the dimensions of this rectangle will return the same numerical height if the element is hidden or not. This can be used to retrieve jQuery's outerHeight value for an element.

Important note: use of this method will perform CSS calculations that can trigger a browser reflow. Therefore, use of this property during an animation frame is discouraged. See also: Browser Reflow

changes.name: changes
changes.comment:
The stream of change records to this object. Records will be delivered asynchronously.

nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.deliverChanges can be called to force synchronous delivery.

children.name: children
children.comment:
List of the direct children of this element.

This collection can be used to add and remove elements from the document.

var item = new DivElement();
item.text = 'Something';
document.body.children.add(item) // Item is now displayed on the page.
for (var element in document.body.children) {
  element.style.background = 'red'; // Turns every child of body red.
}

classes.name: classes
classes.comment:
The set of CSS classes applied to this element.

This set makes it easy to add, remove or toggle the classes applied to this element.

element.classes.add('selected');
element.classes.toggle('isOnline');
element.classes.remove('selected');

client.name: client
client.comment: Gets the position of this element relative to the client area of the page.

contentEdge.name: contentEdge
contentEdge.comment:
Access this element's content position.

This returns a rectangle with the dimenions actually available for content in this element, in pixels, regardless of this element's box-sizing property. Unlike nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.getBoundingClientRect, the dimensions of this rectangle will return the same numerical height if the element is hidden or not.

Important note: use of this method will perform CSS calculations that can trigger a browser reflow. Therefore, use of this property during an animation frame is discouraged. See also: Browser Reflow

dataset.name: dataset
dataset.comment:
Allows access to all custom data attributes (data-*) set on this element.

The keys for the map must follow these rules:

  • The name must not begin with 'xml'.
  • The name cannot contain a semi-colon (';').
  • The name cannot contain any capital letters.

Any keys from markup will be converted to camel-cased keys in the map.

For example, HTML specified as:

<div data-my-random-value='value'></div>

Would be accessed in Dart as:

var value = element.dataset['myRandomValue'];

See also:

  • Custom data attributes

documentOffset.name: documentOffset
documentOffset.comment:
Provides the coordinates of the element relative to the top of the document.

This method is the Dart equivalent to jQuery's offset method.

hasObservers.name: hasObservers
hasObservers.comment: True if this object has any observers, and should call nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.notifyChange for changes.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

marginEdge.name: marginEdge
marginEdge.comment:
Access the dimensions and position of this element's content + padding + border + margin box.

This returns a rectangle with the dimenions actually available for content in this element, in pixels, regardless of this element's box-sizing property. Unlike nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.getBoundingClientRect, the dimensions of this rectangle will return the same numerical height if the element is hidden or not. This can be used to retrieve jQuery's outerHeight value for an element.

Important note: use of this method will perform CSS calculations that can trigger a browser reflow. Therefore, use of this property during an animation frame is discouraged. See also: Browser Reflow

namespaceUri.name: namespaceUri
namespaceUri.comment:
A URI that identifies the XML namespace of this element.

null if no namespace URI is specified.

Other resources

  • Node.namespaceURI from W3C.

nodes.name: nodes
nodes.comment: A modifiable list of this node's children.

offset.name: offset
offset.comment: Gets the offset of this element relative to its offsetParent.

on.name: on
on.comment: This is an ease-of-use accessor for event streams which should only be used when an explicit accessor is not available.

onDrag.name: onDrag
onDrag.comment:
A stream of drag events fired when this element currently being dragged.

A drag event is added to this stream as soon as the drag begins. A drag event is also added to this stream at intervals while the drag operation is still ongoing.

Other resources

  • Drag and drop sample based on the tutorial from HTML5Rocks.

  • Drag and drop specification from WHATWG.

onDragEnd.name: onDragEnd
onDragEnd.comment:
A stream of dragend events fired when this element completes a drag operation.

Other resources

  • Drag and drop sample based on the tutorial from HTML5Rocks.

  • Drag and drop specification from WHATWG.

onDragEnter.name: onDragEnter
onDragEnter.comment:
A stream of dragenter events fired when a dragged object is first dragged over this element.

Other resources

  • Drag and drop sample based on the tutorial from HTML5Rocks.

  • Drag and drop specification from WHATWG.

onDragLeave.name: onDragLeave
onDragLeave.comment:
A stream of dragleave events fired when an object being dragged over this element leaves this element's target area.

Other resources

  • Drag and drop sample based on the tutorial from HTML5Rocks.

  • Drag and drop specification from WHATWG.

onDragOver.name: onDragOver
onDragOver.comment:
A stream of dragover events fired when a dragged object is currently being dragged over this element.

Other resources

  • Drag and drop sample based on the tutorial from HTML5Rocks.

  • Drag and drop specification from WHATWG.

onDragStart.name: onDragStart
onDragStart.comment:
A stream of dragstart events fired when this element starts being dragged.

Other resources

  • Drag and drop sample based on the tutorial from HTML5Rocks.

  • Drag and drop specification from WHATWG.

onDrop.name: onDrop
onDrop.comment:
A stream of drop events fired when a dragged object is dropped on this element.

Other resources

  • Drag and drop sample based on the tutorial from HTML5Rocks.

  • Drag and drop specification from WHATWG.

paddingEdge.name: paddingEdge
paddingEdge.comment:
Access the dimensions and position of this element's content + padding box.

This returns a rectangle with the dimenions actually available for content in this element, in pixels, regardless of this element's box-sizing property. Unlike nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.getBoundingClientRect, the dimensions of this rectangle will return the same numerical height if the element is hidden or not. This can be used to retrieve jQuery's innerHeight value for an element. This is also a rectangle equalling the dimensions of clientHeight and clientWidth.

Important note: use of this method will perform CSS calculations that can trigger a browser reflow. Therefore, use of this property during an animation frame is discouraged. See also: Browser Reflow

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

shadowRoot.name: shadowRoot
shadowRoot.comment:
The shadow root of this shadow host.

Other resources

  • Shadow DOM 101 from HTML5Rocks.

  • Shadow DOM specification from W3C.

templateInstance.name: templateInstance
templateInstance.comment: Gets the template instance that instantiated this node, if any.

xtag.name: xtag
xtag.comment:
Experimental support for web components. This field stores a reference to the component implementation. It was inspired by Mozilla's x-tags project. Please note: in the future it may be possible to extend Element from your class, in which case this field will be deprecated.

If xtag has not been set, it will simply return this nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Element.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart:core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

append.name: append
append.comment:
Adds a node to the end of the child nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.nodes list of this node.

If the node already exists in this document, it will be removed from its current parent node, then added to this node.

This method is more efficient than nodes.add, and is the preferred way of appending a child node.

appendHtml.name: appendHtml
appendHtml.comment: Parses the specified text as HTML and adds the resulting node after the last child of this element.

appendText.name: appendText
appendText.comment: Adds the specified text after the last child of this element.

bind.name: bind
bind.comment: Binds the attribute nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.bind.name to nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.bind.value. nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.bind.value can be a simple value when nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.bind.oneTime is true, or a nuxeo_api_playground/observe-src-bindable.Bindable like nuxeo_api_playground/observe-src-path_observer.PathObserver. Returns the nuxeo_api_playground/observe-src-bindable.Bindable instance.

clone.name: clone
clone.comment:
Returns a copy of this node.

If nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.clone.deep is true, then all of this node's children and decendents are copied as well. If nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.clone.deep is false, then only this node is copied.

createFragment.name: createFragment
createFragment.comment:
Create a DocumentFragment from the HTML fragment and ensure that it follows the sanitization rules specified by the validator or treeSanitizer.

If the default validation behavior is too restrictive then a new NodeValidator should be created, either extending or wrapping a default validator and overriding the validation APIs.

The treeSanitizer is used to walk the generated node tree and sanitize it. A custom treeSanitizer can also be provided to perform special validation rules but since the API is more complex to implement this is discouraged.

The returned tree is guaranteed to only contain nodes and attributes which are allowed by the provided validator.

See also:

  • nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.NodeValidator
  • nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.NodeTreeSanitizer

createShadowRoot.name: createShadowRoot
createShadowRoot.comment:

deliverChanges.comment: Synchronously deliver pending nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.changes. Returns true if any records were delivered, otherwise false.

detached.name: detached
detached.comment:

getComputedStyle.name: getComputedStyle
getComputedStyle.comment:
The set of all CSS values applied to this element, including inherited and default values.

The computedStyle contains values that are inherited from other sources, such as parent elements or stylesheets. This differs from the nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.Element.style property, which contains only the values specified directly on this element.

PseudoElement can be values such as ::after, ::before, ::marker, ::line-marker.

See also:

  • CSS Inheritance and Cascade
  • Pseudo-elements

getDestinationInsertionPoints.name: getDestinationInsertionPoints
getDestinationInsertionPoints.comment:

getElementsByClassName.name: getElementsByClassName
getElementsByClassName.comment:

getNamespacedAttributes.name: getNamespacedAttributes
getNamespacedAttributes.comment:

This is primarily useful for SVG attributes such as xref:link.

insertAdjacentHtml.name: insertAdjacentHtml
insertAdjacentHtml.comment:
Parses text as an HTML fragment and inserts it into the DOM at the specified location.

The nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.insertAdjacentHtml.where parameter indicates where to insert the HTML fragment:

  • 'beforeBegin': Immediately before this element.
  • 'afterBegin': As the first child of this element.
  • 'beforeEnd': As the last child of this element.

  • 'afterEnd': Immediately after this element.

    var html = '<div class="something">content</div>'; // Inserts as the first child document.body.insertAdjacentHtml('afterBegin', html); var createdElement = document.body.children0; print(createdElement.classes0); // Prints 'something'

See also:

  • nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.insertAdjacentText
  • nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.insertAdjacentElement

insertAdjacentText.name: insertAdjacentText

matchesWithAncestors.comment: Checks if this element or any of its parents match the CSS selectors.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.noSuchMethod in an dart:core.Invocation. If nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart:core.NoSuchMethodError.

notifyChange.name: notifyChange
notifyChange.comment:
Notify observers of a change.

For most objects nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.notifyPropertyChange is more convenient, but collections sometimes deliver other types of changes such as a nuxeo_api_playground/observe-src-list_diff.ListChangeRecord.

Notes: - This is not required for fields if you mixin or extend nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Observable, but you can use it for computed properties. - Unlike nuxeo_api_playground/observe-src-change_notifier.ChangeNotifier this will not schedule nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.deliverChanges; use nuxeo_api_playground/observe-src-observable.Observable.dirtyCheck instead.

notifyPropertyChange.name: notifyPropertyChange
notifyPropertyChange.comment:
Notify that the field name of this object has been changed.

The nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.notifyPropertyChange.oldValue and nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.notifyPropertyChange.newValue are also recorded. If the two values are equal, no change will be recorded.

For convenience this returns nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.notifyPropertyChange.newValue.

offsetTo.name: offsetTo
offsetTo.comment:
Provides the offset of this element's nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.borderEdge relative to the specified nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.offsetTo.parent.

This is the Dart equivalent of jQuery's position method. Unlike jQuery's position, however, nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.offsetTo.parent can be any parent element of this, rather than only this's immediate nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.Element.offsetParent. If the specified element is not an offset parent or transitive offset parent to this element, an dart:core.ArgumentError is thrown.

query.name: query
query.comment: Alias for nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.querySelector. Note this function is deprecated because its semantics will be changing in the future.

queryAll.name: queryAll
queryAll.comment: Alias for nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.querySelectorAll. Note this function is deprecated because its semantics will be changing in the future.

querySelector.name: querySelector
querySelector.comment:
Finds the first descendant element of this element that matches the specified group of selectors.

nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.querySelector.selectors should be a string using CSS selector syntax.

// Gets the first descendant with the class 'classname'
var element = element.querySelector('.className');
// Gets the element with id 'id'
var element = element.querySelector('#id');
// Gets the first descendant [ImageElement]
var img = element.querySelector('img');

For details about CSS selector syntax, see the CSS selector specification.

querySelectorAll.name: querySelectorAll
querySelectorAll.comment:
Finds all descendent elements of this element that match the specified group of selectors.

nuxeo_api_playground/nx_batch_reference.Polymer.querySelectorAll.selectors should be a string using CSS selector syntax.

var items = element.querySelectorAll('.itemClassName');

For details about CSS selector syntax, see the CSS selector specification.

scrollIntoView.name: scrollIntoView
scrollIntoView.comment:
Scrolls this element into view.

Only one of of the alignment options may be specified at a time.

If no options are specified then this will attempt to scroll the minimum amount needed to bring the element into view.

Note that alignCenter is currently only supported on WebKit platforms. If alignCenter is specified but not supported then this will fall back to alignTop.

setInnerHtml.comment:

If the default validation behavior is too restrictive then a new NodeValidator should be created, either extending or wrapping a default validator and overriding the validation APIs.

The treeSanitizer is used to walk the generated node tree and sanitize it. A custom treeSanitizer can also be provided to perform special validation rules but since the API is more complex to implement this is discouraged.

The resulting tree is guaranteed to only contain nodes and attributes which are allowed by the provided validator.

  • nuxeo_api_playground/dart:html.NodeTreeSanitizer
